And you can import images <-assets/icon2.svg-> as inline text

Also you can use **bold**, *italic* or ***both***

![Image](https://placehold.net/main.svg)
You can use images from a URL
![Image](assets/foto.png)
or from the assets folder
![A alternative if the image dont load](assets/fotoquenoexiste.png)
Also you can put a URL
[Example](https://example.com)
And you can go to a heading in your document like a URL but with #id instead of the URL
[H2](#2)
You can link to another page on your document like the heading but with pages/path/to/the/page/from/pages (remember the .html) [Introduction](pages/Introduction MMX.html) the introduccion
And also a link to a heading in another page pages/path/to/the/page/from/pages#headingId [Introduction H2](pages/Introduction MMX.html#2")

